605
00:40:14,290 --> 00:40:18,454
The consequence is
that people dropped out of it.

606
00:40:18,661 --> 00:40:22,153
Things changed a great deal
and all that was left was the myth,

607
00:40:22,365 --> 00:40:24,128
the name Comando Vermelho.

608
00:40:24,334 --> 00:40:29,931
<i>Now, we have the frightening
myth of the Comando Vermelho.</i>

609
00:40:33,609 --> 00:40:37,101
<i>They tried to reorganize
in prison.</i>

610
00:40:37,914 --> 00:40:39,438
It didn't work.

611
00:40:39,649 --> 00:40:41,844
Fortunately for us,
it didn't work.

612
00:40:42,218 --> 00:40:45,745
<i>It didn't sparkle.</i>

613
00:40:45,989 --> 00:40:49,925
It went bad because they'd
deviate from it, using drugs and so on.

614
00:40:54,430 --> 00:40:56,193
<i>-I'm a criminal, all right!
-Why?</i>

615
00:40:56,399 --> 00:40:59,197
Why?
Because I like good things.

616
00:40:59,402 --> 00:41:02,064
I was never into being
oppressed by society.

617
00:41:02,271 --> 00:41:05,035
There's no way society
will oppress me.

618
00:41:05,241 --> 00:41:07,641
What I have was not given
to me by society.

619
00:41:07,844 --> 00:41:09,641
-I got on my own.
-What did you get?

620
00:41:09,846 --> 00:41:14,215
With about 3 bank robberies,
I got my own house,

621
00:41:14,417 --> 00:41:16,317
thank God,
and some other things.

622
00:41:16,519 --> 00:41:19,249
We don't want to take people's lives,
we want our own money.

623
00:41:19,455 --> 00:41:22,356
I won't work for US$ 50 a month.

624
00:41:22,625 --> 00:41:25,287
My grandmother is over 70 years old.

625
00:41:25,495 --> 00:41:27,759
She worked her whole life.
What did she get?

626
00:41:27,964 --> 00:41:31,798
She doesn't have anything.
What kind of society is this?

627
00:41:32,001 --> 00:41:34,663
I want a Mizuno tennis shoe.
It costs over US$ 100.

628
00:41:34,871 --> 00:41:36,668
If I work,
I'll never buy a Mizuno.

629
00:41:36,873 --> 00:41:40,536
I'll rob money then.
I'm not scorning the workers,

630
00:41:40,743 --> 00:41:42,904
but I'll rob from people
who have money.

631
00:41:43,913 --> 00:41:46,973
They don't amount to nothing.

632
00:41:47,583 --> 00:41:50,450
They are the tip of the system.

633
00:41:50,653 --> 00:41:52,280
They're excluded from society.

634
00:41:52,488 --> 00:41:56,925
When they're alive,
they control all of that.

635
00:41:57,126 --> 00:41:58,491
When they die, it's over.

636
00:41:58,694 --> 00:42:01,663
Jorge Luiz's son has no
guarantee that he'll become

637
00:42:01,864 --> 00:42:04,924
Acari's drug lord.

638
00:42:05,902 --> 00:42:08,268
<i>They don't even have that.</i>

639
00:42:08,504 --> 00:42:12,497
<i>It's a retail operation.</i>

640
00:42:12,708 --> 00:42:15,142
<i>A favela leader like UÊ is
