641
00:42:15,344 --> 00:42:16,333
<i>He doesn't even know
how to manage profits.</i>

642
00:42:16,546 --> 00:42:19,140
<i>How is UÊ going
to manage US$ 5 million?</i>

643
00:42:19,816 --> 00:42:23,343
He's just the guy
who handles the tent.

644
00:42:23,553 --> 00:42:25,384
That's all he is.

645
00:42:26,189 --> 00:42:29,818
<i>He handles 50 street market tents.</i>

646
00:42:32,228 --> 00:42:34,594
It's basic, isn't it?

647
00:42:35,131 --> 00:42:39,795
<i>No criminal got rich,
bought land and stuff.</i>

648
00:42:40,002 --> 00:42:41,799
<i>They don't stay on
the media spot light either.</i>

649
00:42:42,004 --> 00:42:45,235
Actually, if we analyze it,
we'll see that

650
00:42:45,441 --> 00:42:48,569
the dealer sell drugs

651
00:42:48,778 --> 00:42:54,239
for a clientele in his own community.
Do you understand?

652
00:42:55,351 --> 00:42:57,512
<i>Drug dealing doesn't
bring any transformation</i>

653
00:42:57,720 --> 00:43:00,587
<i>dealers don't change anything,</i>

654
00:43:00,790 --> 00:43:02,690
they are lost in the middle
of the whole thing.

655
00:43:02,892 --> 00:43:07,386
Their inconformity grows and
fades in 24 hours. It's short-lived.

656
00:43:10,867 --> 00:43:15,827
If you check the history of
either the Terceiro Comando

657
00:43:16,038 --> 00:43:17,369
or the Comando Vermelho,

658
00:43:17,573 --> 00:43:20,201
you'll see that neither

659
00:43:20,409 --> 00:43:23,936
had a social background.

660
00:43:24,147 --> 00:43:26,411
They defend their
own interests.

661
00:43:26,616 --> 00:43:29,414
<i>They don't have
a political view of society.</i>

662
00:43:29,619 --> 00:43:34,147
They are like wild animals
fighting to see who is stronger.

663
00:43:35,691 --> 00:43:38,626
<i>Drug dealing does not
